The paper discusses the use of computer vision and machine learning algorithms for X-ray security imaging, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and computer security and cryptography (cs.CR) categories. The paper focuses on deep learning algorithms, which are a subset of machine learning, and therefore, the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) are also likely. The paper also discusses the use of X-ray datasets and performance benchmarks, which falls under the information retrieval (cs.IR) category.
